pageContext.claim: “What we've done in the last three years with the FDA and even the speed of what we're doing, it would take 12, 13, 14 years to get things approved. It’s down to a much smaller number.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump’s Food and Drug Administration is approving generic drugs at a record clip, but we couldn't find support for his claim that the process once took up to 14 years and is now much shorter.
